---
description: Canonical naming for locations (cities), offices, and code identifiers
alwaysApply: true
---

# Naming conventions

| UI term | Meaning | Code / Firestore (keep these identifiers) | Avoid |
|---------|---------|---------------------------------------------|--------|
| **Location** | City / market sub-account | `branch`, `branchId`, `BranchSwitcher`, `homeBranchId`, `branches/{id}` | Calling an office a Location |
| **Office** | Where a Location operates from (deadhead / map) | `officeAddressLine` on Branch; synced `FleetLocation` doc `locations/office` | Separate Garages product UI; “depot” in new copy |
| **Dispatch** | Live ops board / map | `/dashboard/dispatch` | Using “Dispatch” for buildings or cities |

Field names must stay consistent across platforms: `branchId`, `homeBranchId`, `branchIds`, `defaultBranchId`, `canAccessAllBranches`.

License limit `maxLocations` caps the number of **Locations** (branch documents), not offices.
